## Running Tests
Run the Locust test using:
```bash
locust -f [projectFolder]/locustfile.py --host=<TARGET_HOST>
```
Replace `<TARGET_HOST>` with your target server URL.

## Alternate: Running Tests
 This bash file will contain the commands to run each project and more importantly keep an historical report html file 
```
./run_[projectFolder name].sh  
```

## Reporting
Locust provides a web UI for monitoring test performance at 'http://localhost:8089'.

All config folders are ignored. CI/CD will have its own configs.